  volume       = 28,
  number       = 23,
  pages        = {3150--3152},
  issn         = {1367-4811},
  doi          = {10.1093/bioinformatics/bts565},
  abstract     = {SUMMARY: CD-HIT is a widely used program for
    clustering biological sequences to reduce sequence redundancy and
    improve the performance of other sequence analyses. In response to
    the rapid increase in the amount of sequencing data produced by
    the next-generation sequencing technologies, we have developed a
    new CD-HIT program accelerated with a novel parallelization
    strategy and some other techniques to allow efficient clustering
    of such datasets. Our tests demonstrated very good speedup derived
    from the parallelization for up to {$\sim$}24 cores and a
    quasi-linear speedup for up to {$\sim$}8 cores. The enhanced
