    use. Methods When searching nucleotide sequences, VSEARCH uses a
    fast heuristic based on words shared by the query and target
    sequences in order to quickly identify similar sequences, a
    similar strategy is probably used in USEARCH. VSEARCH then
    performs optimal global sequence alignment of the query against
    potential target sequences, using full dynamic programming instead
    of the seed-and-extend heuristic used by USEARCH. Pairwise
    alignments are computed in parallel using vectorisation and
    multiple threads. Results VSEARCH includes most commands for
    analysing nucleotide sequences available in USEARCH version 7 and
    several of those available in USEARCH version 8, including
